## Building for Production

{% if framework == "astro" %}
```bash
npm run build       # Outputs to dist/
npm run preview     # Preview the production build locally
```
{% elif framework == "nextjs-static" %}
```bash
npm run build       # Runs next build + next export, outputs to out/
npx serve out       # Preview the exported static files
```
{% elif framework == "hugo" %}
```bash
hugo                # Outputs to public/
```
{% elif framework == "eleventy" %}
```bash
npm run build       # Outputs to _site/
```
{% endif %}

## Deployment

Target platform: **{{ deploy_target }}**

{% if deploy_target == "vercel" %}
The project is configured for Vercel. Connect the repository in the Vercel dashboard - it detects the framework automatically.

For CLI deployment:
```bash
npm install -g vercel
vercel --prod
```
{% elif deploy_target == "netlify" %}
The project is configured for Netlify. Connect the repository in the Netlify dashboard or use the CLI:

```bash
npm install -g netlify-cli
netlify deploy --prod
```

A `netlify.toml` with the correct build command and publish directory is included.
{% elif deploy_target == "github-pages" %}
Deployment is handled by the GitHub Actions workflow in `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`. Push to `main` to trigger a build and deploy to the `gh-pages` branch.

Ensure GitHub Pages is configured to serve from the `gh-pages` branch in your repository settings.
{% elif deploy_target == "cloudflare-pages" %}
The project is configured for Cloudflare Pages. Connect the repository via the Cloudflare dashboard (Workers & Pages > Create application > Pages > Connect to Git).

Build settings:
- Build command: `{{ 'npm run build' if framework != 'hugo' else 'hugo' }}`
- Build output directory: `{{ 'dist' if framework == 'astro' else ('out' if framework == 'nextjs-static' else ('_site' if framework == 'eleventy' else 'public')) }}`
{% endif %}

## Editing Content

{% if site_type == "docs" %}
Documentation pages live in `src/content/docs/`. Add `.md` or `.mdx` files and they appear in the navigation automatically (depending on framework configuration).
{% elif site_type == "blog" %}
Blog posts live in `src/content/blog/`. Each file is a post. Set `draft: true` in frontmatter to hide a post from the published site.
{% elif site_type == "landing-page" %}
The landing page content is in `src/pages/index.{{ 'astro' if framework == 'astro' else ('tsx' if framework == 'nextjs-static' else 'md') }}`. Component sections are in `src/components/sections/`.
{% elif site_type == "portfolio" %}
Project entries live in `src/content/projects/`. Add a new `.md` file for each project.
{% endif %}

See [docs/content-guide.md](docs/content-guide.md) for full frontmatter reference and content conventions.

{% if use_cms %}
## Content Management

This site uses **{{ cms_type }}** as its content source.

{% if cms_type == "markdown-files" %}
Content is stored as Markdown files in `src/content/`. Edit files directly and commit to publish. The schema for each content type is validated at build time.
{% elif cms_type == "headless-cms" %}
Content is fetched from the headless CMS at build time. Set the CMS API credentials in `.env.local`:

```
CMS_API_URL=https://your-cms.example.com/api
CMS_API_TOKEN=your-token-here
```
{% elif cms_type == "git-based" %}
Content is managed through a git-based CMS interface (such as Decap CMS). The admin panel is available at `/admin` when the site is deployed. Authentication is handled via the deployment platform's identity service.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{% if use_i18n %}
## Internationalization

The site supports multiple languages. Translations are organized by locale:

```
src/content/
  en/     # English (default)
  fr/     # French
  de/     # German (add more as needed)
```

The default locale is English. To add a new language, duplicate the `en/` directory, rename it to the locale code, and translate the content.
{% endif %}

